> This sirloin steak is seasoned with Herbs de Provence—a blend of aromatics from the south of France that includes lavender, rosemary, and tarragon. Together, the meat and aromatics create some truly extraordinary flavors that feel right at home next to the dynamic sides—roasted potatoes and carrots, a rich pan sauce, and a dollop of truffle-flavored sour cream.

== Roasted Carrots and Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch pieces. Pat @sirloin steak{14%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Let sit at room temperature until ready to cook.

Place potatoes and carrots on opposite sides of a #baking sheet{}. Toss each with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide veggies between two baking sheets; roast potatoes on top rack and carrots on middle rack.)

== Truffle Cream ==

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, and @truffle zest{0.07%ounce} (start with a pinch, taste, and add more if desired). Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Steak and Pan Sauce ==

Pat steak dry with paper towels again. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until nicely browned on first side, ~{3-6%minutes}. Flip and lower heat to medium. Add @Herbes de Provence{1%tablespoon} (2 tsp for 4 servings; we sent more) and @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4) to pan. Carefully tilt pan toward you. Using a #spoon{}, continually baste steak with butter until it reaches desired doneness, ~{6-9%minutes} more.

Transfer steak to a #cutting board{} and let rest, keeping any remaining butter in pan. Heat same pan over medium-high heat and add scallion whites and shallot. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup} to pan. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Divide sliced steak, potatoes, and carrots between plates. Stir any resting juices from steak into pan sauce. Drizzle sauce over steak and garnish with scallion greens. Serve with truffle cream on the side for dipping.